1
00:00:01,310 --> 00:00:03,840
(Episode 69)

2
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:08,650
(Breaking News: A Video
of Dream Hotel CEO's Abuse of Power!)

3
00:00:09,780 --> 00:00:11,620
An abuse of power video?
This is ridiculous!

4
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:14,890
How could this happen?

5
00:00:18,520 --> 00:00:21,130
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho. Don't tell me you...

6
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:23,700
I was just trying to contain the damage.

7
00:00:27,970 --> 00:00:31,140
- Father, are you here about the news?
- CEO Chae.

8
00:00:31,970 --> 00:00:35,710
What on earth have you been doing?

9
00:00:53,690 --> 00:00:54,690
Father.

10
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:58,560
- Please, let me explain.
- There's nothing to explain!

11
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:02,800
Are you telling me that's not you
in the video?

12
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,000
It's not like that.
There were extenuating circumstances.

13
00:01:06,070 --> 00:01:07,510
What circumstances?

14
00:01:08,210 --> 00:01:12,510
As the CEO, you should be building up
the hotel's reputation,

15
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:16,010
but instead you abuse your power
and tarnish the hotel's image?

16
00:01:16,380 --> 00:01:17,850
And you still call yourself the CEO?

17
00:01:18,150 --> 00:01:21,790
- This is utterly humiliating!
- Grandfather, please calm down.

18
00:01:22,450 --> 00:01:24,290
Your blood pressure will spike
and you'll collapse.

19
00:01:24,420 --> 00:01:27,260
Since Lawyer Kang Baek Ho is here,

20
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:28,790
keep the stock price from falling
at all costs.

21
00:01:29,660 --> 00:01:30,960
Make sure you handle this!

22
00:01:31,860 --> 00:01:33,500
Lawyer Kang, I'm counting on you.

23
00:01:34,170 --> 00:01:35,170
Yes, I understand.

24
00:01:39,570 --> 00:01:42,840
Lawyer Kang,
welcome to the Dream Hotel Legal Team.

25
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:44,310
I look forward to working with you.

26
00:01:50,950 --> 00:01:51,950
Lawyer Kang,

27
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:54,490
how do you think
we should respond to this?

28
00:01:55,390 --> 00:01:58,660
I'm not sure if the company
has a crisis response manual,

29
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:02,790
but it's an issue of the CEO's integrity,
so you must tread carefully.

30
00:02:04,130 --> 00:02:05,700
Since there's clear evidence,

31
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:10,000
even if you claim it's a deepfake,
it will only add fuel to the fire.

32
00:02:10,340 --> 00:02:13,300
- Then what do you expect me to do?
- Start with a public apology.

33
00:02:14,270 --> 00:02:15,940
A sincere one to the contract employee.

34
00:02:16,710 --> 00:02:20,410
- Right now, this is your best option.
- You want me to apologize?

35
00:02:20,980 --> 00:02:25,220
- I'm the CEO of this hotel.
- Do as Lawyer Kang says!

36
00:02:25,380 --> 00:02:28,790
Of all the times to be
abusing your power as CEO...

37
00:02:28,790 --> 00:02:30,290
and causing a scandal!

38
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:32,760
Are you trying to tank
the company's stock price?

39
00:02:35,730 --> 00:02:36,730
Consider it done.

40
00:02:46,740 --> 00:02:47,770
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

41
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,910
Seriously!

42
00:02:55,610 --> 00:02:56,710
That darn contract worker.

43
00:02:57,080 --> 00:03:00,180
That darn old man had the nerve
to pull a stunt like this?

44
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:03,890
I don't think the elderly worker
was the one who leaked the video.

45
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:07,360
- I just confirmed it myself.
- If it wasn't him,

46
00:03:08,060 --> 00:03:11,330
then who has the guts
to pull a stunt like this?

47
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:14,130
That parking garage
is for executives only.

48
00:03:14,370 --> 00:03:15,430
I looked into it,

49
00:03:15,770 --> 00:03:17,700
and it was most likely filmed...

50
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:20,040
from the spot
diagonally across from yours.

51
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,110
What?

52
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,140
Whose spot is that?

53
00:03:23,940 --> 00:03:24,940
That's...

54
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:28,480
- Seo Rin's spot.
- Seo Rin's?

55
00:03:30,150 --> 00:03:32,220
Are you saying Seo Rin was the one?

56
00:03:32,550 --> 00:03:35,090
I'm not sure.
I'll have to investigate further.

57
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:40,060
You don't think she's Oh Jang Mi, do you?

58
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:42,490
CEO Chae, you've checked for yourself
several times.

59
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:44,560
Oh Jang Mi is still in a coma.

60
00:03:45,430 --> 00:03:48,900
Besides, didn't you say Seo Rin
played the violin for your son?

61
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,200
Gosh, you're right.

62
00:03:52,470 --> 00:03:54,970
I can't believe I was humiliated like that
in front of my own son.

63
00:03:56,770 --> 00:03:58,840
Wait a minute, Manager Lee.

64
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:03,550
Then couldn't this all be something
Jin Hong Ju cooked up?

65
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:05,650
That's it.

66
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:09,550
Jin Hong Ju recommended Kang Baek Ho
to the Legal Team, after all.

67
00:04:11,020 --> 00:04:12,660
Jin Hong Ju and Yeom San Wol.

68
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,690
This must be their doing for sure.

69
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,660
You got the Chairman to back you,

70
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:20,330
and dragged Kang Baek Ho into this,
didn't you?

71
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:23,370
My goodness, what's all this?

72
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:27,340
Chae Hwa Young really stepped in it
this time.

73
00:04:27,470 --> 00:04:31,680
- CEO Chae's true colors. A power trip.
- I know, right?

74
00:04:32,380 --> 00:04:37,150
A leopard can't change its spots.
Old habits die hard.

75
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:38,820
She'd slap me at the drop of a hat.

76
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:41,650
Tell me about it.
I can't count how many times she hit me.

77
00:04:41,790 --> 00:04:44,260
Geum Soon, why do you still stick around
after all that?

78
00:04:45,090 --> 00:04:47,830
For that matter,
why are you still here, Mrs. Yeom?

79
00:04:47,890 --> 00:04:50,560
Gosh, you always have
to get the last word in.

80
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:53,260
But don't you think CEO Chae
has been acting strange?

81
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,630
- Strange how?
- That chef from the other day.

82
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:59,440
He's the general manager now, isn't he?
I'm talking about when he came by.

83
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:03,410
She just tied the general manager's hands
with her scarf.

84
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:07,550
That's right. I remember that.
I was so shocked.

85
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:09,880
My goodness.

86
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:13,450
Hwa Young has a thing for younger men.

87
00:05:13,550 --> 00:05:18,360
But he's young enough to be her son!
How scandalous.

88
00:05:19,260 --> 00:05:20,790
My dear Oh Tae Pyung, too...

89
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:23,800
How old is he again?

90
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:25,600
What's so scandalous about it?

91
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:26,930
Things like that can happen.

92
00:05:28,670 --> 00:05:29,670
For goodness' sake.

93
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:34,340
Controversy grows over a new video
of Dream Hotel's CEO Chae abusing power.

94
00:05:34,610 --> 00:05:37,280
The video in question contains scenes
of shouting and humiliating language,

95
00:05:37,340 --> 00:05:40,880
as well as physical assault and threats
of professional retaliation.

96
00:05:41,010 --> 00:05:43,350
It has sent a shockwave
of outrage across the country.

97
00:05:43,650 --> 00:05:44,720
CEO Chae.

98
00:05:45,150 --> 00:05:47,920
Your wicked true nature
is finally starting to come to light.

99
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:54,330
To think she pretended to help
just to get close to us and do all that...

100
00:05:56,260 --> 00:05:57,860
makes my blood boil. It really does.

101
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:00,360
Tae Pyung.

102
00:06:01,470 --> 00:06:04,340
- Our Tok Hee is asleep.
- Mom.

103
00:06:05,370 --> 00:06:08,840
The enemy who did this to you.
I'll make sure they pay for it.

104
00:06:09,270 --> 00:06:11,840
- Just wait a little longer.
- Who's the enemy?

105
00:06:12,340 --> 00:06:15,550
- We must have a gunfight with the enemy.
- Okay, okay.

106
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:16,880
Just wait, Mom.

107
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:22,420
Perfect timing.
I was just wondering about you.

108
00:06:22,490 --> 00:06:23,690
My, Mr. Tae Pyung.

109
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:27,990
- You were wondering about me?
- His name is Oh Tae Pyung.

110
00:06:30,290 --> 00:06:33,300
No, that's not what I meant.

111
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:36,430
What do you mean? It's nice to be missed.

112
00:06:36,570 --> 00:06:40,540
That's how all great stories begin,
with a little curiosity. Right?

113
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:43,840
What is this lady talking about?

114
00:06:44,110 --> 00:06:45,940
Your eyes look weird.

115
00:06:48,580 --> 00:06:51,080
I was wondering why you hadn't come by
for side dishes.

116
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:55,550
Mom's side dishes are really good today.
You should try some.

117
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:58,160
Just buy something and leave.
Jang Mi's exhausted.

118
00:06:58,220 --> 00:07:02,230
- She needs to eat some of Mom's food.
- My, that passionate gaze.

119
00:07:02,590 --> 00:07:04,130
What do I do?

120
00:07:04,460 --> 00:07:07,430
I don't know what to do with myself.
Okay, fine.

121
00:07:07,730 --> 00:07:11,540
You don't have to wait for me,
I'll come every day from now on.

122
00:07:11,770 --> 00:07:12,770
How's that?

123
00:07:15,710 --> 00:07:16,740
Yes.

124
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:17,740
Hope you enjoyed your meal.

125
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:19,180
Please come again!

126
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:21,780
(Bomdama)

127
00:07:28,050 --> 00:07:29,090
Tae Pyung.

128
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:32,420
You should bring Mom and Bo Ra
to eat here.

129
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:33,960
(Bomdama)

130
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:41,070
Tae Sook.

131
00:07:41,370 --> 00:07:43,530
I knew you'd be successful,
but I didn't think it'd be this big.

132
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:45,800
This place is so spacious and beautiful.

133
00:07:45,870 --> 00:07:48,740
Thanks. It's so crowded today,

134
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:51,910
- so it's a bit chaotic.
- The meat is delicious.

135
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:56,480
- It's so delicious! Can I have some more?
- This is my third plate already.

136
00:07:56,980 --> 00:08:00,180
It's great everyone can pick and choose
what they want.

137
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:02,590
I'm going to book my next get-together
here in advance.

138
00:08:02,650 --> 00:08:03,650
Okay.

139
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:06,720
Looks like our plan was a success.

140
00:08:07,330 --> 00:08:08,690
I feel so relieved.

141
00:08:09,060 --> 00:08:11,660
But I have a feeling
CEO Chae will try to pull something.

142
00:08:11,900 --> 00:08:15,700
Still, she's lost Chairman Ma's trust,
so the damage is significant.

143
00:08:15,930 --> 00:08:18,500
- The public is turning against her too.
- It's all thanks to you.

144
00:08:19,370 --> 00:08:22,010
I wonder how Chae Hwa Young
will even try to apologize.

145
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:23,740
She'll have no choice but to apologize.

146
00:08:24,910 --> 00:08:25,910
Cheers!

147
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:31,680
What are you two being
so lovey-dovey about?

148
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:38,660
We were discussing CEO Chae's scandal.
The whole hotel is in an uproar.

149
00:08:38,890 --> 00:08:40,560
What else would we be talking about?

150
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:46,800
I'm worried we'll lose all our guests.
Especially coming from the CEO.

151
00:08:46,930 --> 00:08:49,170
She of all people should be focused
on promoting the hotel.

152
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Team Leader Jin.

153
00:08:52,540 --> 00:08:55,010
Are you badmouthing my mother
right in front of me?

154
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:59,040
Gosh, no.

155
00:08:59,340 --> 00:09:04,280
I'm just worried about
the hotel losing guests.

156
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:09,590
Baek Ho, can I talk to you for a second?

157
00:09:10,190 --> 00:09:11,190
With me?

158
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,870
You've never been here before, have you?

159
00:09:29,510 --> 00:09:31,140
Yes, pretty much.

160
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:35,680
- Should we set up a desk for you here?
- A desk for me?

161
00:09:36,150 --> 00:09:38,180
But I'm with the Dream Group's Legal Team.

162
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:41,050
The Chairman said you should come over
to the Hotel and work here on assignment.

163
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:42,350
Really?

164
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,320
Well then,

165
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:48,090
I'd like to sit right here.

166
00:09:49,930 --> 00:09:50,930
No.

167
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,600
Over here.

168
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,630
I think next to me would be better.

169
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,530
CEO Chae wants to see me.

170
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:59,000
Okay.

171
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:00,570
Lawyer Kang,

172
00:10:01,210 --> 00:10:04,110
thanks for everything today.
I'll see you around.

173
00:10:04,310 --> 00:10:05,810
Yes, Director Ma. Well then...

174
00:10:06,380 --> 00:10:07,380
I'll be on my way.

175
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:15,190
What's with them?
They look way too friendly.

176
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:16,720
So irritating.

177
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:21,330
For the hotel's sake,
you need to issue a public apology.

178
00:10:22,930 --> 00:10:27,600
It's a deepfake video.
This fake news is trying to ruin my life.

179
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:32,270
AI technology has gotten so advanced.
Even you know that, Lawyer Kang.

180
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:33,700
As I mentioned earlier,

181
00:10:34,410 --> 00:10:36,170
trying to pass this off as a deepfake
is not a viable strategy.

182
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:39,610
Along with a formal apology...

183
00:10:40,210 --> 00:10:42,150
and offer to rehire the employee involved,

184
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,320
how about we arrange a press conference?

185
00:10:45,550 --> 00:10:48,220
I've drafted a plan along those lines,
so please follow my lead.

186
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:49,290
An apology?

187
00:10:49,890 --> 00:10:51,460
There's no way I'm doing that.

188
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:55,360
If I apologize,
it's like admitting they won.

189
00:10:55,990 --> 00:11:00,100
Besides, I have nothing to apologize for.

190
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:11,040
- Hey.
- So, what's your damage control plan?

191
00:11:11,580 --> 00:11:14,950
CEO Chae's the one who made this mess,
so why do I have to clean up her mess?

192
00:11:15,450 --> 00:11:18,080
Hey, that's literally your job.

193
00:11:18,450 --> 00:11:21,790
And you're supposed to do it
for the company, not for CEO Chae.

194
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:23,220
I know.

195
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:26,690
I'm trying to handle it,
but she insists she did nothing wrong...

196
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:28,590
and is digging in her heels,
refusing to apologize.

197
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:30,330
Just give it some time.

198
00:11:30,690 --> 00:11:33,230
Even the CEO Chae will see
she has no choice but to apologize.

199
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:36,270
You talk like you're
some kind of enlightened sage.

200
00:11:36,330 --> 00:11:38,070
You don't have any corporate experience.

201
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:41,610
You spent your life sheltered by Mom,
just helping people in need,

202
00:11:41,940 --> 00:11:44,340
Never worrying about money
or what other people think,

203
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:46,910
you've always been so carefree and naive.

204
00:11:48,010 --> 00:11:50,480
So, you really think that's how
I've lived my whole life?

205
00:11:50,820 --> 00:11:55,650
That I'm oblivious to the dark side
of the world and just live in a bubble?

206
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,490
- Me?
- Am I wrong?

207
00:11:57,560 --> 00:12:00,490
You have no idea
why I help people who are struggling.

208
00:12:01,490 --> 00:12:04,900
Forget it. You only know
the surface-level me.

209
00:12:05,330 --> 00:12:06,330
This kid.

210
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,570
You make it sound like
there's some big secret.

211
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:11,300
Don't tell me...

212
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,100
Don't tell me what?

213
00:12:14,610 --> 00:12:18,840
If you have feelings for Director Ma,
I won't let you have her, not even you.

214
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:21,180
Never mind.

215
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:24,680
You should go. I'm taking a half-day off,
so I have a lot to get done.

216
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:26,680
Yes, okay.

217
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:28,220
Wait a second.

218
00:12:30,190 --> 00:12:32,360
This is for you.
You know what I mean, right?

219
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:34,060
Don't overdo it.

220
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:40,600
He's just impossible to hate.

221
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,070
If I had grown up with my birth parents,

222
00:12:50,470 --> 00:12:52,910
I wonder if I could have been
as carefree as you.

223
00:12:57,550 --> 00:12:59,450
Dad, she's the one fooling you.

224
00:13:00,180 --> 00:13:01,750
Think about it, okay?

225
00:13:02,190 --> 00:13:03,250
Could it really be...

226
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:05,660
that Hwa Young...

227
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,660
is really this kind of person?

228
00:13:14,370 --> 00:13:16,170
Do you not know who I am?

229
00:13:16,870 --> 00:13:19,970
- No, that's not what I meant...
- Wherever I park becomes my spot.

230
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:22,440
How dare you tell the CEO what to do?

231
00:13:23,370 --> 00:13:26,280
You're so clueless. No wonder
you still get yelled at at your age.

232
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:27,480
That's not it.

233
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:32,120
You have to park in a designated spot.
Otherwise, you'll be blocking other cars.

234
00:13:32,180 --> 00:13:33,950
And who exactly am I inconveniencing?

235
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:38,760
Why let someone so dim-witted and pathetic
handle the parking?

236
00:13:39,460 --> 00:13:41,760
One could hire anyone off the street
for an hourly wage.

237
00:13:43,460 --> 00:13:45,000
I'm going to have you fired immediately.

238
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,600
CEO Chae, I was wrong.

239
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:50,900
I need this job.
If I lose it, we'll starve.

240
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:54,070
- So please...
- Get your hands off me! The nerve.

241
00:13:55,340 --> 00:13:57,270
CEO Chae.

242
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:00,280
My goodness.

243
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:06,680
Is this really who Hwa Young is?
All this time, have I been...

244
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:08,990
completely wrong about her?

245
00:14:09,690 --> 00:14:10,890
Like Baek Ho said,

246
00:14:11,490 --> 00:14:13,820
with Oh Bok Gil's accident,
did CEO Chae...

247
00:14:14,590 --> 00:14:16,030
just use me?

248
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:24,100
I wonder if flowers recognize
a beautiful person on sight.

249
00:14:24,570 --> 00:14:26,940
The air is thick with their scent.

250
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:31,110
Just getting in?

251
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:34,780
You should at least greet
your mother-in-law when you see her.

252
00:14:36,150 --> 00:14:39,950
Then again, I guess you have no shame,
after dragging our company through mud.

253
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:43,320
I guess you're in no state to be polite.
Oh my!

254
00:14:43,620 --> 00:14:45,660
What the heck do you think you're doing?

255
00:14:46,490 --> 00:14:48,190
Oh! My face!

256
00:14:48,730 --> 00:14:51,300
Greet you? You've got to be kidding me.

257
00:14:51,730 --> 00:14:54,430
You have some nerve running your mouth
after slandering me behind my back.

258
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:58,140
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- Don't play dumb with me.

259
00:14:58,770 --> 00:15:02,370
Did you think I wouldn't find out
that you two leaked that power trip video?

260
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:05,380
Where's Hong Ju? Me, on a power trip?

261
00:15:05,540 --> 00:15:08,880
Who do you think you are, a freeloader,
to pull a stunt like that?

262
00:15:09,580 --> 00:15:12,350
You really think you can get away with it
and still live in this house?

263
00:15:13,450 --> 00:15:17,050
You've completely lost it.
Why bring Hong Ju into this?

264
00:15:17,290 --> 00:15:21,230
Anyone can see that's just how you act.
Stop playing the victim.

265
00:15:22,060 --> 00:15:24,760
I give you an inch and you take a mile.
Have you no respect?

266
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:27,100
Take this!

267
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:33,800
Don't hit people, not even with a flower.
Don't you know that?

268
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:36,240
You think you're the only one
who can throw her weight around?

269
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:40,480
I know times changed and daughters-in-law
rule the roost these days,

270
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:44,080
but this has gone too far.
I'll teach you to fear your mother-in-law.

271
00:15:45,450 --> 00:15:48,190
Yeom San Wol. Let me warn you.

272
00:15:48,690 --> 00:15:51,090
Keep running that mouth of yours
and see what happens.

273
00:15:51,460 --> 00:15:53,360
You really think you can take me on?

274
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:57,630
That's right, I am.
What are you going to do about it?

275
00:15:57,700 --> 00:15:59,660
I have nothing left to lose now, either.

276
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,030
You're already framing me for something
I didn't do, so what's stopping me now?

277
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:07,400
You're the one on a power trip,
so why are you taking it out on us?

278
00:16:07,470 --> 00:16:10,410
- Why?
- How dare you talk back to me?

279
00:16:11,140 --> 00:16:14,140
You and your daughter have been scheming
and waiting for a chance to backstab me.

280
00:16:14,210 --> 00:16:15,350
Did you think I wouldn't know?

281
00:16:16,510 --> 00:16:19,420
Unbelievable.
She keeps blaming an innocent person.

282
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:24,620
Who backstabbed you?
This is so unfair, I could scream.

283
00:16:24,690 --> 00:16:25,790
Cut the act.

284
00:16:26,490 --> 00:16:28,260
It was you and your damn daughter.

285
00:16:28,860 --> 00:16:30,790
You two will regret this.

286
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:33,630
Ma'am, get dinner ready.

287
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:36,770
I'm starving after dealing
with these two all day.

288
00:16:37,370 --> 00:16:38,370
Yes, ma'am.

289
00:16:40,970 --> 00:16:41,970
Chae Hwa Young!

290
00:16:48,380 --> 00:16:51,550
Now you get a taste of your own medicine.
See how you like being hit with flowers.

291
00:16:52,950 --> 00:16:54,490
What do you think you're doing?
You little!

292
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:57,320
- Gosh, seriously.
- Let go.

293
00:16:57,890 --> 00:16:59,790
- My goodness.
- Let go already!

294
00:17:01,530 --> 00:17:02,560
- My goodness
- You started this.

295
00:17:04,430 --> 00:17:06,200
- Let go of me.
- What do you two think you're doing?

296
00:17:29,550 --> 00:17:31,420
Aren't you ashamed of yourselves
in front of the children?

297
00:17:32,690 --> 00:17:35,930
It's disgraceful.
What on earth is going on here?

298
00:17:36,530 --> 00:17:39,230
Honey, I swear this is unfair.

299
00:17:39,460 --> 00:17:43,730
I have a clear conscience.
But that power trip video.

300
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:46,170
She's accusing me and Hong Ju
of leaking that video.

301
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:49,540
- A thief won't just confess.
- Quiet.

302
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:52,840
CEO Chae, you have no room to talk.

303
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:56,350
You should be lying low,
still acting high and mighty?

304
00:17:56,650 --> 00:18:00,880
Are you aware Dream's stock price
is plummeting because of you?

305
00:18:01,150 --> 00:18:02,150
I apologize.

306
00:18:02,220 --> 00:18:05,160
Don't apologize to me.
You need to apologize to the victim...

307
00:18:05,220 --> 00:18:08,630
and issue a public apology.
You need to take proper measures.

308
00:18:10,260 --> 00:18:12,500
As for your one percent share
in the company,

309
00:18:13,230 --> 00:18:14,600
it will be transferred to Yeom San Wol.

310
00:18:15,530 --> 00:18:16,570
Chairman?

311
00:18:16,830 --> 00:18:17,840
Honey.

312
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:21,100
- You're finally giving me...
- You have nothing to complain about.

313
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:24,680
If the CEO, our company's public face,
causes a scandal like that,

314
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:28,480
she must face the consequences.
If you're not happy with that,

315
00:18:28,910 --> 00:18:31,520
then take responsibility
and resign as CEO.

316
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:36,090
From now on, CEO Chae,
every time you damage the company's image,

317
00:18:36,390 --> 00:18:37,990
you'll hand over one percent
of your shares.

318
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:41,260
Words are cheap.
Anyone can say they're sorry.

319
00:18:41,590 --> 00:18:43,130
You have to be held accountable.

320
00:18:43,460 --> 00:18:47,100
That's why I put you in that position,
to take responsibility. Understand?

321
00:18:53,170 --> 00:18:54,710
CEO Chae's one percent stake?

322
00:18:55,340 --> 00:18:56,740
That's a huge deal.

323
00:18:57,010 --> 00:18:58,210
My grandfather's pretty amazing, isn't he?

324
00:18:58,480 --> 00:19:01,550
Yes, this is going to be
a huge blow to CEO Chae.

325
00:19:01,650 --> 00:19:03,680
Once Chae Hwa Young's true colors
are revealed to the world,

326
00:19:04,150 --> 00:19:06,680
when we reveal she's the one
who murdered my father,

327
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:10,190
- everyone will believe us, right?
- You did a great job.

328
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:14,860
- I already miss you, Jang Mi.
- What are you saying?

329
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,230
We just saw each other.

330
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:22,800
Who's on the phone
that's making you smile like that?

331
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:25,540
Team Leader Jin, aren't you heading home?

332
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:27,140
I was just about to.

333
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:30,710
You can go on ahead.
I still have a few things to finish up.

334
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:33,010
Okay, I have to go.

335
00:19:34,140 --> 00:19:35,250
I'm just so curious.

336
00:19:36,110 --> 00:19:37,110
I was just wondering...

337
00:19:37,610 --> 00:19:39,520
Jang Mi hasn't woken up, has she?

338
00:19:40,550 --> 00:19:41,550
What?

339
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:43,250
It was just a random thought.

340
00:19:43,590 --> 00:19:45,890
It's just that you had
such a big smile on your face.

341
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,230
I have to be more careful.

342
00:19:57,770 --> 00:19:58,770
Seriously.

343
00:19:59,370 --> 00:20:00,470
This is absurd.

344
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:05,310
So if I don't apologize,
he'll take my shares and my CEO title?

345
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:08,450
So that old man is playing hardball now,
is that it?

346
00:20:09,010 --> 00:20:10,010
Darn it.

347
00:20:10,650 --> 00:20:11,650
Gosh, that hurts.

348
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:16,920
(Daemyung Medical Center)

349
00:20:17,220 --> 00:20:18,690
About 30 years ago,

350
00:20:19,060 --> 00:20:21,430
I was treated for Leukemia
at this hospital.

351
00:20:22,090 --> 00:20:23,930
I was wondering if you might still have
my medical records.

352
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:27,360
I heard they're usually destroyed
after ten years.

353
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:30,770
For serious conditions like leukemia,

354
00:20:31,170 --> 00:20:32,700
we keep the records permanently.

355
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:34,810
That's a relief.

356
00:20:35,370 --> 00:20:38,140
At the time of my treatment,
my name was Kim Young Ho,

357
00:20:38,580 --> 00:20:41,610
but I changed it to Kang Jun Ho
after I was adopted.

358
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:43,680
Is that so?

359
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:48,220
I brought the official documents
proving the name change.

360
00:20:50,190 --> 00:20:51,190
One moment, please.

361
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:53,460
Kim Young Ho.

362
00:20:55,130 --> 00:20:56,960
We do have a record,

363
00:20:57,160 --> 00:21:00,760
but since it's so old,
it might be stored separately.

364
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:04,330
(Happy Children's Home)

365
00:21:05,870 --> 00:21:08,740
By any chance, is the guardian's name...

366
00:21:09,040 --> 00:21:11,740
or the name of the home I was at?

367
00:21:14,180 --> 00:21:16,810
The guardian is listed
as a foster care agency.

368
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:23,350
You said you used to live here?

369
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:26,120
I believe I was adopted
from Tanjin Children's home,

370
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:28,790
but was returned and then sent here.

371
00:21:29,260 --> 00:21:30,490
What was your name back then?

372
00:21:30,830 --> 00:21:32,130
Back when I was here,

373
00:21:32,630 --> 00:21:34,430
my name was Kim Young Ho.

374
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,640
Kim Young Ho?

375
00:21:39,370 --> 00:21:40,600
Would you like to take a look?

376
00:21:42,610 --> 00:21:43,870
(Child Welfare Card, Kim Young Ho)

377
00:21:43,940 --> 00:21:46,010
That's him. That's my son.

378
00:21:46,510 --> 00:21:47,510
Ha Neul.

379
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:49,380
My son, Ha Neul.

380
00:21:53,220 --> 00:21:56,890
I've finally found you.
I'm so sorry, Ha Neul.

381
00:22:02,530 --> 00:22:05,900
(Diagnosed with Leukemia)

382
00:22:07,930 --> 00:22:09,700
What's this?

383
00:22:14,040 --> 00:22:17,640
A sick child, hospitalized for leukemia...

384
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:21,410
- Right?
- That's right. That was me.

385
00:22:21,780 --> 00:22:24,080
My goodness, you're alive.
You're really alive.

386
00:22:25,380 --> 00:22:26,820
I'm so thankful you're alive.

387
00:22:28,820 --> 00:22:32,360
- What do you mean?
- Oh, dear. I feel terrible.

388
00:22:32,990 --> 00:22:36,260
A fine young man like you, alive and well,

389
00:22:37,430 --> 00:22:40,760
but I only saw the note about you
being hospitalized for leukemia...

390
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:43,130
and I went and told her
you must have passed away.

391
00:22:44,940 --> 00:22:47,870
Are you saying someone came here
looking for me?

392
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:07,520
Hello?

393
00:23:08,460 --> 00:23:09,460
Director.

394
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:12,700
What did you just say?

395
00:23:13,460 --> 00:23:16,000
You're saying my son came there
looking for me?

396
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:20,070
Yes. You seemed so desperate
to find your son,

397
00:23:20,540 --> 00:23:24,610
so I went ahead and gave him
your phone number.

398
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:25,840
You shouldn't have!

399
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:28,110
Why would you give him my number?

400
00:23:28,450 --> 00:23:32,020
- Why would you do something like that?
- Excuse me?

401
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:37,320
Call him right now and tell him
I absolutely cannot meet him. Got it?

402
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:41,560
Jun Ho.

403
00:23:42,130 --> 00:23:45,130
So you really have been missing me.
My son.

404
00:23:49,930 --> 00:23:51,200
But Jun Ho...

405
00:23:52,770 --> 00:23:55,610
Right now, I'm not in a position
to face you.

406
00:24:04,750 --> 00:24:05,750
I don't know how to tell you this.

407
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:08,620
Your mother said that
she doesn't want to meet you.

408
00:24:09,190 --> 00:24:10,620
She also asked you not to call.

409
00:24:11,420 --> 00:24:14,760
What kind of person gives birth to a child
only to abandon them?

410
00:24:15,360 --> 00:24:18,730
She goes to all the trouble of finding me,
only to refuse to meet me now?

411
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:22,100
It's not like I was dying
to meet her anyway.

412
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,670
Any news on what I asked you to look into?

413
00:24:30,570 --> 00:24:34,510
The leaked dashcam footage,
and the photos and messages sent around.

414
00:24:35,450 --> 00:24:39,950
- Wasn't it Yeom San Wol and Jin Hong Ju?
- I don't think so.

415
00:24:40,620 --> 00:24:44,590
We're tracing the sender's number,
but it's bound to be a burner phone.

416
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:46,120
Besides,

417
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:49,290
this is too sophisticated
for Yeom San Wol and Team Leader Jin.

418
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:50,930
If it wasn't them,

419
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:54,930
that means there's someone else out there
who's a threat to me.

420
00:24:57,370 --> 00:25:00,240
It has to be Oh Jang Mi.
I'm telling you, she's awake.

421
00:25:00,740 --> 00:25:01,810
That's not confirmed yet.

422
00:25:02,370 --> 00:25:03,910
I'll look into it.

423
00:25:05,580 --> 00:25:08,080
If Oh Tae Pyung was the one
who blackmailed Professor Kang,

424
00:25:08,650 --> 00:25:11,950
then those two siblings are coming
after me with a vengeance.

425
00:25:12,120 --> 00:25:15,250
It means they're behind everything
that's happened.

426
00:25:16,390 --> 00:25:18,490
Oh Jang Mi has to be awake.

427
00:25:19,420 --> 00:25:20,820
Oh Jang Mi is awake?

428
00:25:24,530 --> 00:25:26,360
- I'm home!
- Tae Pyung's here!

429
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:31,170
- You already paid?
- Yes, I paid for a full year upfront.

430
00:25:31,230 --> 00:25:33,500
Hey, you have that kind of money?

431
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:38,810
- Who? Do you have a secret sugar mama?
- You bet I do.

432
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:42,050
Ok Hee and Tok Hee are rich.
Tae Pyung's rich.

433
00:25:42,110 --> 00:25:46,520
- Mom, are we rich too?
- Yes, I guess life's pretty good.

434
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:49,550
I wish every day could be just like this.

435
00:25:51,860 --> 00:25:56,130
- Welcome!
- Tae Sook's the owner and she's rich too.

436
00:25:58,700 --> 00:26:00,660
Mom, you're the owner
of the restaurant, right?

437
00:26:00,660 --> 00:26:02,570
I'm going to go brag at preschool.

438
00:26:03,930 --> 00:26:07,640
Excuse me, aren't you Oh Jang Mi?

439
00:26:07,740 --> 00:26:08,940
What? Me?

440
00:26:10,110 --> 00:26:11,270
No, I'm not.

441
00:26:11,910 --> 00:26:14,140
But how do you know my Jang Mi?

442
00:26:14,380 --> 00:26:17,450
I'm just a regular here.

443
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:20,250
My Jang Mi is in the hospital right now.

444
00:26:20,350 --> 00:26:22,990
Tok Hee's sleeping
at Korea University Hospital.

445
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:29,260
(Korea University Hospital)

446
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:41,070
So this is Oh Jang Mi?

447
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:48,450
What the?

448
00:26:49,350 --> 00:26:51,350
Wait, what's Ma Seo Rin doing here?

449
00:26:53,750 --> 00:26:55,620
(Name: Oh Jang Mi)

450
00:26:56,790 --> 00:26:58,460
Seriously, what's going on?

451
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:03,630
Oh Jang Mi looks exactly like Ma Seo Rin.

452
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:07,160
What, they're twins?

453
00:27:13,970 --> 00:27:14,970
Thank you.

454
00:27:15,540 --> 00:27:19,810
If it weren't for you, Baek Ho,
I never could've cornered Chae Hwa Young.

455
00:27:21,180 --> 00:27:22,380
You should get some rest now.

456
00:27:23,210 --> 00:27:25,280
You've been fighting
all on your own for so long.

457
00:27:26,280 --> 00:27:29,990
Even Chae Hwa Young won't find it easy
to get away without apologizing this time.

458
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:33,560
Honestly, I just want
to get this revenge over with...

459
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:35,730
and go back to my mom.

460
00:27:36,630 --> 00:27:37,630
Well, for now...

461
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:39,900
how about resting in my arms?

462
00:27:40,630 --> 00:27:41,700
What was that?

463
00:27:42,270 --> 00:27:43,330
Gosh, so cheesy!

464
00:28:55,540 --> 00:28:57,340
(The First Man)

465
00:28:57,410 --> 00:28:58,880
Are they really twins?

466
00:28:59,110 --> 00:29:00,640
Go see for yourself, Mom.

467
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:02,750
See if I was wrong
or if they're really twins.

468
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:05,850
I'll go to the hospital
first thing tomorrow and see for myself.

469
00:29:06,220 --> 00:29:08,080
You know you've been acting
really strange lately, right?

470
00:29:08,550 --> 00:29:09,650
Are you seeing someone else?

471
00:29:10,390 --> 00:29:14,260
I'm a seasoned divorce lawyer.

472
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:17,660
First thing tomorrow morning,
we need to get rid of Oh Jang Mi.

473
00:29:17,790 --> 00:29:19,260
I have to get there
before Chae Hwa Young does.

474
00:29:19,860 --> 00:29:21,530
If I'm a step behind,
Seo Rin will be in danger.

475
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:25,470
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
